# Coding Rules for this Nuxt 4 Project

## General Rules
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` for all components and pages
- Never use `any` in TypeScript - define proper interfaces/types
- Follow strict TypeScript mode (noImplicitAny, strictNullChecks)

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., AppHeader.vue, AppTable.vue)
- Pages: kebab-case (e.g., user-profile.vue)
- Composables: camelCase starting with `use` (e.g., useUsers.ts)
- Variables/Functions: camelCase

## Nuxt Auto-imports
- Do NOT manually import: ref, computed, useFetch, useAsyncData, definePageMeta, $fetch, defineEventHandler, readBody, createError
- These are auto-imported by Nuxt

## Fetching Data
- Use `useFetch` or `useAsyncData` for data fetching
- Do NOT use axios or manual fetch
- Use `<NuxtLink>` instead of `<a>` for internal navigation

## Server API
- Use `defineEventHandler` for API route handlers
- Import prisma from `~/server/lib/prisma`
- Always validate input data
- Return proper HTTP status codes

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design

## Database
- Use Prisma ORM for all database operations
- Always handle errors gracefully
- Validate data before database operations